      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Hamburg, ¶  ¶ 7 November ¶  ¶ 1856 ¶ Most esteemed ¶  ¶ Professor, ¶  ¶  ¶ More than a year ago I sent you a manuscript ¶  ¶ for ¶  ¶ the Plantae Muellerianae. I always hoped to see the same printe...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">M56.11.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Wilhelm Sonder to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Diederich von Schlechtendal</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">MS not seen; text given here extracted from Tkach, Neubauer &amp; Roser (2022), Brief</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">29</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Hamburg d.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>7<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Novb.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>56</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Geehrtester Herr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Professor!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vor länger denn einem Jahre übersandte ich Ihnen Manuskript zu den Plantae Müllerianae. Ich hoffte immer dasselbe gedruckt zu sehen u hätte gerne noch in diesem Herbst die Abdrucke nach Australien befördert, damit Dr. Müller bei seiner Rückkehr von der Nord-Expedition, die im nächsten Frühjahr vielleicht schon stattfinden kann, solche vorfinden möchte. Sie werden mir deshalb nicht verargen, wenn ich mir erlaube, Sie an das Manuskript zu erinnern. Die Bearbeitung der kleinen Familie der Pittosporeen ist schon wieder fertig, durch einen hiesigen Herren Klatt, den ich damit gerne in die Wissenschaft einführen möchte. Ich befürchte meine Bearbeitung fallen nun auch mit den von J. D. Hooker in der Flora Tasmaniae zusammen, wodurch wieder unnöthige Synonymen entstehen. Um dieses zu verhüten, hat Prof. Miquel die Müller’schen Myrtaceen, Loranthaceen<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Conifera<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>etc. kürzlich in Holland drucken lassen. Im September Heft des Journal of Botany beschreibt Mitten die Müller’schen Moose aus Victoria, wodurch verschiedene Hampe’sche Namen zu Synonymen werden.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ihrem freundlichen Andenken<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>empfiehlt sich</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>hochachtungsvoll</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Sonder</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hamburg,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>7 November<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1856</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Most esteemed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Professor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>More than a year ago I sent you a manuscript<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Plantae Muellerianae. I always hoped to see the same printed and would have liked to have sent the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reprints to Australia this autumn so that Dr. Mueller<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>might perhaps already<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>find them on his return from the northern expedition, which<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>take place next spring. You will therefore not blame me if I take the liberty of reminding you of the manuscript. The treatment of the small family of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Pittosporeae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is already<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>completed by a local gentleman, Mr Klatt, whom I would like to introduce to science<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it. I am afraid that my work will now coincide with that of J. D. Hooker in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Flora Tasmaniae</seg>, which will again lead to unnecessary synonyms. To prevent this, Prof. Miquel has recently had the Mueller Myrtaceae, Loranthaceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Conifera<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Coniferae; Miquel (1856).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>etc. printed in Holland. In the September<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>issue of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of Botany</seg>, Mitten describes the Mueller mosses from Victoria, whereby various Hampe names become synonyms.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To your friendly memory<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>takes leave.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Sonder</p>
         </div>
      </body>
